==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quint
<hw>Quint</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>quinte</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>quintus</ets>, <ets>quinta</ets>, the fifth,
<ets>quinque</ets> five. See <er>Five</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
set or sequence of five, as in piquet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The interval of a fifth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>one of a set of <er>quintuplets</er>.</def>
<mark>[informal]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quintain</ent>⟦br⟧
